3000|$|For what {{concerns}} the MAC layer, J. Alonso-Zrate et al., in [...] "Persistent RCSMA: a MAC protocol for a distributed cooperative ARQ scheme in wireless networks," [...] present the persistent relay <b>carrier</b> <b>sensing</b> <b>multiple</b> <b>access</b> (PRCSMA) protocol {{that allows for}} the execution of a distributed cooperative automatic retransmission request (ARQ) scheme in IEEE 802.11 wireless networks. The underlying idea of the PRCSMA protocol is to modify the basic rules of the IEEE 802.11 MAC protocol to execute a distributed cooperative ARQ scheme in wireless networks to enhance their performance and to extend coverage.|$|R
